{"descriptions":[{"id":1283,"title":null,"content":"\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eNumber is never marked in verbs, adjectives, or the majority of nouns. Plurality is usually implied either by context, or by quantifiers such as \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eམང་པོ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;many\u0026rdquo;; \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཚང་མ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;all\u0026rdquo;; \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eག་ཤས་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;some,\u0026rdquo; \u0026ldquo;certain\u0026rdquo;; \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eགཉིས་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;two,\u0026rdquo; etc.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eHowever, there is a plural marker \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཚོ་\u003c/span\u003e, which appears with demonstratives and personal pronouns:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eའདི་ཚོ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;These\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eདེ་ཚོ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Those\u0026rdquo; \u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཕ་ཚོ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Those,\u0026rdquo; \u0026ldquo;those over there\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eཁོང་ཚོ་ \u0026ldquo;They,\u0026rdquo; etc.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eThe marker \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཚོ་\u003c/span\u003e by itself is used with nouns denoting people only when the people in question are specified/defined:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཨ་མ་ཚོ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;The mothers\u0026rdquo; \u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eདགེ་རྒན་ཚོ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;The teachers\u0026rdquo; \u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eསློབ་གྲྭ་བ་ཚོ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;The students\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eThe non-specific plural is not marked with the plural particle:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཨ་མ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Mothers\u0026rdquo; \u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eདགེ་རྒན་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Teachers\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eFurthermore, this suffix is not used with animals or inanimate objects:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e*\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eལུག་ཚོ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;[The] sheep\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e*\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཅོག་ཙེ་ཚོ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;[The] tables\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e*\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཐང་ཀ་ཚོ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;[The] tangkas\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eConsequently, unambiguous renderings of the plural or indications of plurality require the use of demonstratives:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eལུག་དེ་ཚོ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Those sheep\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཅོག་ཙེ་དེ་ཚོ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Those tables\u0026rdquo; \u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eNumber is only marked once per noun or noun phrase; the marker, which is placed at the end of the group, is therefore never redundant.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབུ་མོ་ཆུང་ཆུང་དེ་ཚོ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Those little girls\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eགངས་རི་མཐོ་པོ་དེ་ཚོ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Those high snow-mountains\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཨ་མ་གཞོན་པ་ཚོ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;The young mothers\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eརོགས་པ་གཞན་པ་ཚོ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;The other companions\u0026rdquo; \u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cem\u003eNote\u003c/em\u003e: The following demonstratives also occur in conversation:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eའདི་གྱད་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;These\u0026rdquo; (nearby)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eདེ་གྱད་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Those\u0026rdquo; (distant)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eའདི་གྱད་འདི་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;All these\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eདེ་གྱག་དེ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;All those\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eThese last two expressions are used to make a selection from a group.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eདེབ་འདི་གྱད་འདི་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;All these books\u0026rdquo; (and not the others)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e","source_url":null,"is_primary":true,"created_at":"2013-09-15 04:15:25 UTC","updated_at":"2013-09-15 04:15:25 UTC","authors":[{"id":"6","fullname":"Nicolas Tournadre"}]}]}